<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Bars 0-4 (phrase A): Gm-Dm alternation — the piece is in a Dorian/modal Gm feel despite F key.
  LH consistently open Gm (G2-D3-G3-Bb3) and Dm (D2-A2-D3-F3)
- Bars 5-8 (repeat A): varied inversions — Gm 2nd inv, Dm7, quartal Gm
- Bars 9-11 (phrase B, tonic arrival): F-Dm-Am-Bb descending harmonic sequence
- Bars 12-14 (codetta): C-Dm-Gm final descent, Dm final chord

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bars 1-8: Gm-Dm alternation creates a constant rocking bass motion D2↔G2
- Bar 9: tonic F arrival — first clear I chord, creates structural moment
- Bar 11: C-Bb-F-Bb cadential rocking (V-IV-I-IV = modal plagal progression)
- Bar 14: F→Gm→Dm final — vi substitutes for I in a "feminine ending"

TEXTURE ARC:
- Pickup: single-note RH, sparse 3-note LH
- Bars 1-4: per-beat chords, 2+4 texture
- Bars 5-8: richer inversions, 3-note RH appears in phrase
- Bars 9-13: full 3+4 voicing, climax at bar 11 (C-Bb-F-Bb busy motion)
- Bar 14: convergence to Dm, final 3-beat bar
-->
